The good, are the landscapes, some effects the Effort to Fix what Rian Johnson did...and the falcon.

I thought it was very rushed. It seemed like J.J. Abrams was trying to sweep The Last Jedi under the rug and conclude the Saga. In some ways it works, in other ways it's way too complicated with little time for explanation. I liked it, but it is definitely low on my Star Wars rankings.
Love it so much sticks Landing of the saga

It's pretty stuffed trying to do too many things at the same time (clarify some things, character development, tie a bow on the series, etc). The story is reasonably coherent but in the end, it's not the epic end to a nine-movie series but it does have some of the fun associated with Star Wars movies we've come to expect.

With low expectations but excitement building for the last installment of my childhood, J.J. Abrams rounded out the Skywalker Saga beautifully. No matter who you are or what you want the film to be, know that this is the ending. If we can forgive George Lucas for editing the originals and bringing us the Prequels, we can forgive J.J. any slights/misses we believe he made. Very enjoyable and thought provoking. Left me wanting more!
